@Veneni7

3. Your point about playing black characters is one that the world needs to figure out. Blackface in the US is a tradition that began out of hate. Its signature look is one that Piet shares. But here, it is done out of love of the character. Does one culture ruining it make it universally bad?

In a lot of ways, it reminds me of the swastika, which was a symbol of peace before Nazis changed its meaning in the public eye. Does that permanently brand it as offensive?
